<TITLE> M Ziauddin made special envoy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 24 (bdnews24.com)The government has appointed retired diplomat Mohammad Ziauddin as an ambassador-at-large with the rank of state minister. The cabinet division issued the order on Nov 22. Ziauddin's is the fourth ambassador to enjoy the rank of state minister. The government earlier appointed three envoys to enjoy the rank: Akramul Qader, ambassador to Washington, Sayeedur Rahman Khan, high commissioner to Britain, and Tariq Ahmad Karim, high commissioner to India. Academician Gowher Rivzi, meanwhile, was earlier appointed as prime minister Sheikh Hasina's adviser on foreign affairs with the rank of a cabinet minister.
